layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "label"
description: "Associates a text caption with a form control. Labels are essential for accessibility, enabling screen readers to announce form fields and allowing users to click the label to focus the associated input."
elementName: label
category: native
nativeGroup: Forms
currentPath: /docs/elements/native/label/
permalink: /docs/elements/native/label/
---

{% set explicitLabelCode %}<label for="name">Full Name</label>
<input type="text" id="name" />{% endset %}

{% set implicitLabelCode %}<!-- Text input wrapped -->
<label>
  Email Address
  <input type="email" />
</label>

<!-- Checkbox wrapped -->
<label>
  <input type="checkbox" /> I agree to the terms
</label>{% endset %}

{% set checkboxRadioCode %}<!-- Checkbox -->
<label>
  <input type="checkbox" name="feature" /> Enable feature
</label>

<!-- Radio buttons in fieldset -->
<fieldset>
  <legend>Select size</legend>
  <label>
    <input type="radio" name="size" value="small" /> Small
  </label>
  <label>
    <input type="radio" name="size" value="large" /> Large
  </label>
</fieldset>{% endset %}

{% set requiredFieldCode %}<p class="help">Fields marked with * are required</p>
<label for="name">Name *</label>
<input type="text" id="name" required />{% endset %}

{% set visuallyHiddenCode %}<label for="search" class="visually-hidden">Search</label>
<input type="search" id="search" placeholder="Search..." />{% endset %}

{% set cssReferenceCode %}label {
  display: block;
  font-weight: 500;
  margin-block-end: var(--size-xs);
}

/* Auto-detected checkbox/radio labels */
label:has(input[type="checkbox"]),
label:has(input[type="radio"]) {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--size-xs);
  margin-block-end: 0;
  cursor: pointer;
}

/* Within a .group container */
.group > label {
  font-weight: 500;
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
}

/* Visually hidden but accessible */
.visually-hidden {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 0;
}{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Every <a href="/docs/elements/native/input/">input</a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/select/">select</a>, and <a href="/docs/elements/native/textarea/">textarea</a> needs a label</li>
      <li>Checkboxes and radio buttons should have labels wrapping them</li>
      <li>Any form control that requires user identification</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Always provide labels</strong>. Forms without labels are inaccessible to screen reader users.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>VB Styling</h2>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze styles labels as <code>display: block</code> with <code>font-weight: 500</code> and a small bottom margin (<code>var(--size-xs)</code>). When a label contains a checkbox or radio input, VB auto-detects this via <code>:has()</code> and switches to <code>inline-flex</code> with centered alignment, gap spacing, and a pointer cursor &mdash; no classes needed.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Association Methods</h2>

    <h3>Explicit: Using the <code>for</code> Attribute</h3>
    <p>The recommended method. The label's <code>for</code> attribute matches the input's <code>id</code>.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/label-patterns.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/label" title="Label patterns" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Explicit label association">{{ explicitLabelCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Implicit: Wrapping the Input</h3>
    <p>The label wraps the input. Useful for checkboxes and radios where text follows the control.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Implicit label association">{{ implicitLabelCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With Checkboxes and Radios</h2>
    <p>For checkboxes and radio buttons, wrap the input inside the label. VB auto-detects the contained checkbox or radio via <code>label:has(input[type="checkbox"])</code> and switches the label to <code>inline-flex</code> with proper alignment and a pointer cursor. No extra classes required.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Checkbox and radio labels">{{ checkboxRadioCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Required Field Indicator</h2>
    <p>Indicate required fields visually. The asterisk is commonly used but should be explained at the top of the form.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Required field indicator">{{ requiredFieldCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Visually Hidden Labels</h2>
    <p>When a label is not visually needed (e.g., a search field with a placeholder), hide it visually but keep it accessible with the <code>.visually-hidden</code> utility class.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Visually hidden label">{{ visuallyHiddenCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p class="help">The <code>.visually-hidden</code> class hides the label from sight while keeping it announced by screen readers.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility Notes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Every input needs a label</strong>: No exceptions for accessibility</li>
      <li><strong>Use <code>for</code> attribute</strong>: Explicit association is clearer and more robust than wrapping</li>
      <li><strong>Labels are clickable</strong>: Clicking a label focuses its associated input</li>
      <li><strong>Don't use placeholder as label</strong>: Placeholders disappear when typing</li>
      <li><strong>One label per input</strong>: A single label cannot serve multiple inputs</li>
      <li><strong>aria-labelledby alternative</strong>: Can reference multiple elements for complex labels</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

